MC: PropDistMC1-1
PropDistMC1-1

A student conducts a survey for her class project. She asks 32 other students a series of questions about their study habits. She knows from previous research that 0.51 of all students study for 4 or more hours per day. If 0.3 of her own sample study for 4 or more hours per day, what is the probability of observing this sample proportion or less?
You'll need to correctly distinguish between sample and population when calculating Z for this question. Pick the closest answer.
Z = (phat - p)/sqrt(pq/n). The probability can be found directly from the Z table.
